00:01:15.119 --> 00:01:20.460
terms, democracy has not been the norm. Like
the 20th century was the high tide for democracy

00:01:20.460 --> 00:01:25.469
worldwide with the number of democratic governments
increasing dramatically, but the 2000's so

00:01:25.469 --> 00:01:30.609
far have seen something of a anti-democratic
renaissance with the number of democracies

00:01:30.609 --> 00:01:36.630
that shouldn't actually be called democracies,
doubling between 2006 and 2009. Like the People's

00:01:36.630 --> 00:01:42.299
Democratic Republic of Korea, despite having
democratic in the name, not particularly democratic...

00:01:42.299 --> 00:01:46.460
I'm sorry for saying that Kim Jong-un, but
